        <h4>Claims:</h4>
        <dl>
          
            
            <dt>
              <a href="https://www.factopolis.com/claims/jerry-jones-told-players-to-stand-for-the-anthem-or-be-fired/">Jerry Jones Told Players to Stand for the Anthem or They Would Be Off the Team</a>
            </dt>
            <dd>
              <h5>The Truth:</h5>

              He didn&rsquo;t, though he has voiced disapproval about players not standing for the National Anthem.
            </dd>
          
        </dl>
        
          <h4>Fact Checks:</h4>
          <dl>
            
              
              <dt><a href="http://www.politifact.com/texas/statements/2017/aug/02/greg-abbott/greg-abbott-celebrates-false-claim-jerry-jones-tol/">PolitiFact</a></dt>
              <dd>
                <blockquote>In a 2016 radio interview, Jones aired disappointment in Kaepernick not standing for the anthem. We spotted no confirmation of Jones telling Cowboys players to stand or be gone.</blockquote>
              </dd>
            
          </dl>
        
